          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the three layers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C conventional. Grease and line a 20 cm square tin. Beat the marzipan, butter, and sugar together until smooth. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the flour, baking powder, and salt. Divide the batter into three equal portions. Leave one plain (white), colour one red, and one green. Bake each layer separately in the prepared tin for 10 to 12 minutes until set and barely golden. Slide each layer onto a rack to cool, using the paper to lift it out. Keep the paper under each layer while cooling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sandwich and press",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the green layer on a board and brush with a thin layer of warm apricot jam. Place the white layer on top and brush again with jam. Top with the red layer. Wrap tightly in cling film, place on a flat tray, and press with a heavy weight overnight in the fridge.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Enrobe and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the dark chocolate. Unwrap the pressed block. Spread melted chocolate over the top and all four sides. Set on a rack until the top coat is firm. Flip, coat the base, and allow to set completely. Using a long sharp knife, trim the edges, then cut into strips and across into cookies approximately 4 cm wide. Wipe the knife clean between cuts.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
